<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761504>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Illustrations of morphological characters presented in the Key to the leptodirine leiodid genera of the phyletic series of “Leonhardella” (after Jeannel 1911, 1924; Ćurčić et al. 2008a). A. Absence of mesosternal carina. B. Presence of mesosternal carina. C. Absence of a concavity on mesosternal carina. D. Presence of a deep concavity on mesosternal carina. E. Presence of elliptical body shape. F. Presence of pholeuonoid body shape. G. Presence of dilated protarsi in males. H. Presence of undilated protarsi in males. I. Presence of a short rounded basal projection on basal bulbus. J. Presence of a long subtriangular basal projection on basal bulbus. K. Presence of subglobular antennomere VIII. L. Presence of elongate antennomere VIII. M. Presence of paramerae with two setae. N. Presence of paramerae with three setae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5761504/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

